  carbohydrates: 43 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 37 g
  sodium: 3.8 g
  serving size: 512
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/vegetarian-sausage-cassoulet-5dfca5211413cb766f301737
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed, quartered lengthways and chopped into small pieces). Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g}(thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, high sided pan or #casserole pot{} over high heat. Once hot, add the @Linda McCartney sausages{6} and cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. (You may need to do this in batches). Add a little more oil if the sausages start to stick. Transfer to a plate. Whilst the sausages are cooking, drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%400g can}(drained and rinsed).

Add a drizzle of oil to the now empty pan and add the chopped onion and carrot. Cook, stirring, until softened and turning golden, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the mushrooms and cook for a further ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @wild mushroom paste{1}, @tomato puree{30%g}, @dried thyme{1}, water (see ingredients for amounts) and half the garlic. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Simmer with a lid on for ~{10%minutes}.

Remove the lid from the pan, return the sausages to the cassoulet and simmer until the mixture has thickened, a further ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} over medium to high heat and add the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} with the remaining garlic and cook, stirring, until golden brown and crispy, ~{3-4%minutes}. Tip onto a plate and stir through half the parsley.

Stir the remaining parsley through the cassoulet and divide it between bowls. Scatter over the crispy breadcrumbs. Enjoy!